<div class="faq-section page-width">
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="tab">
    <button class="tablinks active" onclick="openTab(event, 'Shipping')">Shipping & Returns</button>
    <button class="tablinks" onclick="openTab(event, 'Customization')">Customization</button>
    <button class="tablinks" onclick="openTab(event, 'Orders')">Orders</button>
  </div>

  <div id="Shipping" class="tabcontent" style="display:block">
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Where do you ship?</summary>
      <p>We currently ship all over India.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How long will my order take?</summary>
      <p>
        Once your design is approved (for custom orders) or once your order is placed (for ready designs), the delivery
        timeline is 1 to 2 weeks. This allows for printing and shipping time.
      </p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How Can I Track My Order?</summary>
      <p>
        Once your order is printed and shipped (usually within 7–14 days), you’ll get a tracking link via email or
        WhatsApp. If you haven’t received tracking after 10 days, please reach out to us with your order number and
        we’ll check on it ASAP.
      </p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Is there free shipping?</summary>
      <p>
        We do not offer free shipping at the moment. Shipping charges are calculated in the original price of the
        product.
      </p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Do you accept returns or exchanges?</summary>
      <p>
        We do not offer returns or exchanges. As a print-on-demand business, every product is made & printed
        specifically for you. We don’t hold inventory, and each item is unique.
      </p>
    </details>
  </div>

  <div id="Customization" class="tabcontent">
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Do you offer product customization?</summary>
      <p>
        Yes! You can customize a product by reaching out to us via our website email or social media. Simple text
        changes: ₹100 Full design or typography changes: ₹499 Once we understand your request, we take a 50% advance,
        create the design, and share it for approval. We allow 1 round of feedback, and any changes beyond that will be
        charged additionally.
      </p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can I upload my own design?</summary>
      <p>
        Absolutely. You can send us your own artwork to print on our products. However: If edits are needed, charges
        will apply. We are not responsible for print quality if the file you provide is low-resolution or unclear.
      </p>
    </details>
  </div>

  <div id="Orders" class="tabcontent">
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can I cancel my order?</summary>
      <p>
        Since everything is made to order, we do not allow cancellations once an order is confirmed. The only exception
        is if the product goes out of stock before printing begins.
      </p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Are your designs original?</summary>
      <p>
        Yes! All our designs are created in-house. We also welcome customer-submitted ideas or references for custom
        orders.
      </p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Do you take bulk or corporate orders?</summary>
      <p>Yes, we do! Please get in touch with us directly for bulk order discounts and timelines.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>My Payment Was Deducted, But I Haven’t Received A Confirmation. What Should I Do?</summary>
      <p>
        Sometimes, payment gateways take a few minutes to process and confirm an order. If you’ve been charged but
        haven’t received a confirmation email within 30 minutes, please reach out to us with: Your payment receipt or
        screenshot Email ID used for the order Product(s) ordered We’ll check and get back to you within 24 hours.
      </p>
    </details>
  </div>

  <script>
    function openTab(evt, tabName) {
      var i, tabcontent, tablinks;
      tabcontent = document.getElementsByClassName('tabcontent');
      for (i = 0; i < tabcontent.length; i++) {
        tabcontent[i].style.display = 'none';
      }
      tablinks = document.getElementsByClassName('tablinks');
      for (i = 0; i < tablinks.length; i++) {
        tablinks[i].className = tablinks[i].className.replace(' active', '');
      }
      document.getElementById(tabName).style.display = 'block';
      evt.currentTarget.className += ' active';
    }
  </script>
</div>

